<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="114" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="114">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="114">
This species is widely distributed from Europe, where it is considered to be a montane subalpine species, to the Pacific Ocean, including Mongolia, China, and the Korean peninsula. A closely related species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1884" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Leptura" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Leptura mimica" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mimica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">Leptura mimica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bates, 1884 is endemic to Japan and Sakhalin Islands. Its divergence has been confirmed in both morphological and genetic studies (
<bibRefCitation author="Makihara, H" journalOrPublisher="Elytra" pageId="25" pageNumber="132" pagination="5 - 10" refId="B43" refString="Makihara, H, Saito, A, 1985. Studies on Leptura arcuata (1), (Coleopt., Cerambycidae). Elytra 12: 5 - 10" title="Studies on Leptura arcuata (1), (Coleopt., Cerambycidae)." volume="12" year="1985">Makihara and Saito 1985</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Makihara, M" journalOrPublisher="Elytra" pageId="25" pageNumber="132" pagination="5 - 18" refId="B44" refString="Makihara, M, Saito, A, Sato, M, 1991. Studies on the Leptura arcuata species-group (2), (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae). Elytra 19: 5 - 18" title="Studies on the Leptura arcuata species-group (2), (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae)." volume="19" year="1991">Makihara et al. 1991</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Saito, S" journalOrPublisher="Special bulletin of the Japanese Society of Coleopterology" pageId="25" pageNumber="132" pagination="381 - 391" refId="B60" refString="Saito, S, Saito, A, Kim, C-G, Su, Z-H, Osawa, S, 2002. Phylogeny of the Leptura arcuata Complex (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae) as deduced from mitochondrial ND5 gene sequences. Special bulletin of the Japanese Society of Coleopterology 5: 381 - 391" title="Phylogeny of the Leptura arcuata Complex (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae) as deduced from mitochondrial ND 5 gene sequences." volume="5" year="2002">Saito et al. 2002</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.724.20667" author="Rossa, R" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="25" pageNumber="132" pagination="31 - 42" refId="B59" refString="Rossa, R, Goczal, J, Pawliczek, B, Ohbayashi, N, 2017. Hind wing variation in Leptura annularis complex among European and Asiatic populations (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae). ZooKeys 724: 31 - 42, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.724.20667" title="Hind wing variation in Leptura annularis complex among European and Asiatic populations (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.724.20667" volume="724" year="2017">Rossa et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
). The biology of 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. annularis" pageId="7" pageNumber="114" rank="species" species="annularis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">L. annularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to that of the previously described species (
<bibRefCitation author="Svacha, P" journalOrPublisher="Biologica" pageId="26" pageNumber="133" pagination="1 - 205" refId="B64" refString="Svacha, P, Danilevsky, ML, 1989. Cerambycoid larvae of Europe and Soviet Union (Coleoptera, Cerambycoidea). Part III. Acta Universitatis Carolinae. Biologica 32 (1-2): 1 - 205" title="Cerambycoid larvae of Europe and Soviet Union (Coleoptera, Cerambycoidea). Part III. Acta Universitatis Carolinae." volume="32" year="1989">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Švácha">Svacha</normalizedToken>
and Danilevsky 1989
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
